Mrs. Christine King Farris, the sister of Dr. Martin Luther King Jr., passed away in Atlanta. She was an esteemed educator and civil rights leader, actively involved in organizations such as the NAACP and the SCLC. She also served as Vice Chair and Treasurer of the King Center for Nonviolent Social Change. Mrs. Farris was a symbol of America's promise, having been raised by a Black preacher in the Deep South and educated at Spelman College and Columbia University. She stood for peace, freedom, and justice throughout her life. The nation mourns her passing and sends condolences to the King family.